Install GitLab on Ubuntu-16.04
==============================

1. Install and configure the necessary dependencies 

$ sudo apt-get install curl openssh-server ca-certificates postfix

2. Add the GitLab package server and install the package 

$ curl -sS https://packages.gitlab.com/install/repositories/gitlab/gitlab-ce/script.deb.sh | sudo bash
$ sudo apt-get install gitlab-ce

3. Configure and start GitLab 

$ sudo gitlab-ctl reconfigure
need to configure the domain name in the configuration file so you can access GitLab. Open the file.

$ sudo vi  /etc/gitlab/gitlab.rb

In this file edit the 'external_url' and give the server domain. Save the file and then open the newly created GitLab site from a web browser.
Now open browser and type "Local IP of Server (200.0.0.30)"

4. Browse to the hostname/IP-Address and login

On your first visit, you'll be redirected to a password reset screen to provide the password for the initial administrator account. Enter your desired password and you'll be redirected back to the login screen.
The default account's username is root. Provide the password you created earlier and login. After login you can change the username if you wish.(
(For-Old-Release---By default it creates 'root' as the system admin and uses '5iveL!fe' as the password. Log into the GitLab site and then change the password.)

From GUI create additional user(gitadmin) and Project/Repo named as TesT add a file and add some text and commit
Now git Local Git Server is Ready to work

Do some Testing


From Client  clone remote repo,create new branch  and make changes and pull to new branch
=====================================================================================

Log in as any user

$ git clone http://200.0.0.30/gitadmin/TestT.git

$ cd TestT
$ git status
$ ls -la


$ git config --list
$ git config --global user.name "tester"
$ git config --global user.email "tester@test.com"
$ git config --list


$ git checkout -b pro1
$ mkdir wall
$ cp /home/ubuntu/Downloads/FireFox/4*.jpg wall/
$ ls wall/
$ cp /home/ubuntu/Downloads/FireFox/Git-VCS.pdf .

$ git status

$ git add .
$ git commit -m "Addes Files from 200.0.0.10"
$ git status

$ git remote -v

$ git push origin pro1

